Sure! Here’s a simple test code for the ESP32 using the Arduino framework. This code will blink the built-in LED on the ESP32:


```cpp
void setup() {
  pinMode(LED_BUILTIN, OUTPUT); // Initialize the built-in LED pin as an output
}

void loop() {
  digitalWrite(LED_BUILTIN, HIGH); // Turn the LED on
  delay(1000);                     // Wait for a second
  digitalWrite(LED_BUILTIN, LOW);  // Turn the LED off
  delay(1000);                     // Wait for a second
}
```

Feel free to ask if you need more details or a specific type of test code!
